Volumes were split in a set of ipsilateral and contralateral eye preferring neurons by thresholding at an ODI value of 0. For layer 4 volumes, all significantly visually responsive neurons were included, and for layer 2/3 to layer 5 volumes only neurons between 370 and 430 μm in depth were included. Clusters of ipsilateral eye preferring neurons were identified using the ‘fast search and find of density peaks’ algorithm25. In brief, the local density for neuron i (ρi) was calculated following Eq. 2, where N equals the total number of neurons, dij is the Euclidian distance of neurons i and j (μm in cortical space), and dc is a cutoff-distance set to the fifth percentile of the distribution of all local distances. The function \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
